Rhea Myers is an artist, writer and hacker from the UK now based in Vancouver, BC. An early creative and critical adopter of the blockchain, his work centers on the intersection of changing technological, aesthetic and social form. Robs blockchain art projects include Facecoin (2014), Blockchain Aesthetics (2015) and Artworld Ethereum (2014  ongoing). His writing on the subject includes (Conceptual) Art, Cryptocurrency and Beyond (2014), Blockchain Geometries (2018) and the story Bad Shibe (2017).
